Now let's think of it.

00:05:12.340 --> 00:05:13.925
Right now, if you just
saw that, you might say,

00:05:13.925 --> 00:05:15.079
"Oh, maybe this is some type of a line,"

00:05:15.079 --> 00:05:17.900
but we'll see very clearly it's not a line

00:05:17.900 --> 00:05:22.900
because what happens as our
angle gets closer and closer to,

00:05:24.996 --> 00:05:28.700
as our angle gets closer
and closer to pi over two,

00:05:28.700 --> 00:05:30.858
what happens to the slope of this line?

00:05:30.858 --> 00:05:32.033
So that is theta.

00:05:32.033 --> 00:05:34.433
We're getting closer and
closer to pi over two.

00:05:34.433 --> 00:05:36.633
This ray, I guess I should say,

00:05:36.633 --> 00:05:39.500
is getting closer and closer
to approaching the vertical,

00:05:39.500 --> 00:05:43.392
so its slope is getting more
and more and more positive,

00:05:43.392 --> 00:05:45.566
and if you go all the way to pi over two,

00:05:45.566 --> 00:05:47.300
the slope at that point
is really undefined

00:05:47.300 --> 00:05:48.802
but it's approaching,

00:05:48.802 --> 00:05:51.986
one way to think about it is
it is approaching infinity.

00:05:51.986 --> 00:05:53.706
So as you get closer and
closer to pi over two,

00:05:53.706 --> 00:05:55.366
so I'm going to make a ...

00:05:55.366 --> 00:05:57.689
I'm going to draw essentially
a vertical asymptote

00:05:57.689 --> 00:06:00.800
right over here at pi over two

00:06:01.319 --> 00:06:03.500
because it's not going to be ...

00:06:03.500 --> 00:06:04.500
I guess one way we could think about it,

00:06:04.500 --> 00:06:06.233
it's approaching infinity there,

00:06:06.233 --> 00:06:10.263
so this is going to be
looking something like this.

00:06:10.263 --> 00:06:12.900
It's going to be looking
something like this.

00:06:12.900 --> 00:06:14.900
The slope of the ray as
you get closer and closer

00:06:14.900 --> 00:06:18.368
